<br>
HoD/Harvest for another 9 per tick (higher than this on raids)<br>
Mod rod for another 9 per tick<br>
<br>
Both of these take trivial amounts of time, and would be used on a raid.<br>
<br>
Or, 21% more mana regen standing (104) and 17% more sitting (124)<br>
<br>
Mana preservation does random from 1% to 15% mana saved (or so it seems based off casting some VERY high mana cost spells, and seeing the cost vary).<br>
<br>
So, 1360 damage average, and 184 mana average per cast<br>
<br>
Effective ratio of 7.4, or 128 DPS standing and 153 DPS sitting.<br>
<br>
Now, note that Iceflame makes the spears insane ratio city, and the glove-foci make SoS almost as good a ratio.  You lose some -resist, but gain alot of efficiency.<br>
<br>
SoS hits 9.57 effective ratio, and Ancient Ice 10.68.  Just using SoS without Ice would up your sitting DPS to 198, breaking 200 by mixing in some Ice would be relatively easy.  And, as noted, concussion pants make maintaining this level of DPS possible.<br>
